---
description: Repository architecture conventions
globs:
  - "**/*"
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow the monorepo structure:

- apps/web for Next.js frontend
- apps/api for FastAPI backend
- packages/shared-types for frontend/backend shared contracts
- packages/scoring for reusable score definitions and helpers
- docs for product and technical documentation
- infra for Docker and environment setup

Architecture rules:
- keep app-specific code inside apps/*
- keep reusable logic outside app pages/routes where possible
- do not mix UI components with scoring logic
- do not put raw SQL/API glue directly into route handlers
- prefer service modules and pure utility functions
- keep config-driven constants centralized

When adding a new feature, update only the minimum set of files needed while preserving clean separation.
